<DIV>Rain_VZ said: Getting rid of safezones besides the bazaar is the best idea presented yet. With some tweaking, it can work. People will whine that they can't tradeskill or do any quests (they won't be able to for a month) then all the people camping books and harassing people in PoK will get bored and everything will resume as usual. I joined Vallon Zek 4 years ago to pvp not sit in safe zones all day selling buffs and doing tradeskills.</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Rain you obviously aren't looking at the impact of removing all Safe Zones except the Bazaar. The Bazaar has about on average 300-400 people in there, whether on Trader Mode or not. The place is laggy enough as it is. By adding the estimate amount of 200 people from PoK and then the additional 100 from PoTranq, the bazaar will be extra laggy, people LDing all the time, and just think about the zone crashes that will occur when there are about 700 people in one small zone. If you want to PvP more often, zone into PoV or BoT, HoH or more of the higher zones. Aduentus loves to go zone hopping looking for PvP, you can do the same if you wish to pvp more often. There isn't a single day when I am on EQ that I don't experience PvP, if there is one day that you don't experience it, that is when you begin to worry.</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>As Raabe mentioned earlier, PoTranquility is the access point to 19 of the PoP zones. It is because of this zoning being an access point to those 19 PoP zones,that it should remain a non-pvp zone.</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>With regards to the Point System, get rid of that and don't bring it over to VZ. Considering that most of VZ is now 4-teamers, Planar acceleration is now increased, and if you bring that point system over, it will be mainly affecting those who still remain Purist and those who still 3-team.</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Regarding about classes like Shadow Knights, if you want them to nerf HarmTouch, put a small cast time on it. Like if you look at a Necro, their LifeBurn has a cast time. AAs like HT & LB are use more as Finishing Blows to kill the person. Myself being a Cleric, I know not to drop below 75% of HP, and with paying attention to my HP, I have survived several HT in which I was able to Divine Barrier myself to keep myself alive. Little tweaks can go a long way.</DIV>
<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Instead of EQ throwing new expansions every few months, they should first fix up some of the problems that we are facing now. Such as the PoK glitch and what not...</DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							<font color = "lightblue">- <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1201372&resize=true">Lord Etrius Aura`Eminence of Vallon Zek</a><br>70 Erudite Prelate of Quellious<br><a href="http://www.assentguild.com">Assent</a> ~ Maelin Starpyre</font>
