		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			It's not just because it leads to other zones.  For instance, East Commons is one zone that leads to quite a few.  I remember plenty of battles that ranged all around EC.  It's the fact that an entire expansion can be controlled from one small area, which also happens to be inside a building that can be blocked off.  There are no ports in or out of the zones that are connected to it, no other way to access them.  But I hear you say, "LoY is only through one zone!" and you're correct.  But at the levels you can xp and raid in the LoY zones you can also do in other places.  There quite simply is not a viable alternative to PoP at this point.  Both the xp and gear that drop there are vital to further progression in the game and to compete in PvP.  That is why making PoT PvP is a bad idea.
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							Menre Nar'tredok<br>Arch Mage of the Crimson Praetorian<br>Blood and Honor!
