<DIV></DIV>
<P>I use crimson potions, ive tried stinging wart potions.&nbsp; Number 1) when you reach a certain point of the game you start to outregen these potions.&nbsp; Do you know what that means?&nbsp; it means they do not work unless you start stripping regen gear in the middle of pvp.&nbsp; And sometimes people DO go pvping on their own.&nbsp; You stick a crimson potion up and a bard will cure you, click another and they will cure you again.&nbsp; Chanters have gotten smart and all gone out and either farmed or bought shields of the immaculate which are targetable and cure crimson potions on you as well.&nbsp; That makes them next to worthless.&nbsp; No one should have an overpowering spell that can lock down opponents for unlimited time.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>And cambysis, no i dont want to make paladins gods, part of the reason that pallys get stuck up on god level is due to the "old resists".&nbsp; Someone like caliel could run around without the risk of being snared or rooted or even nuked etc, with all the new funky resist checks we are very suceptable to roots/snares/nukes etc.&nbsp; Your lifetap may not do as much as one of our heals, but i would certainly hope not, seeing as yours do damage to the opponent as well as healing you, they shouldnt be as effective as a regular heal.</P>
<P>&nbsp;</P>
<P>And yeah bracelet of secrets needs nerf stick too, 3 second cast time, no recast time on pillage enchantment effect is just silly.</P>
