		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<P>No, make PoTranq a PvP live zone, just give it more than a single access point in or out so a bottleneck isn't created when making it live.&nbsp; There's no reason anyone should be able to pansy out of PvP simply by clicking a stone to safety.&nbsp; You either gate or die, like it or leave.</P>
<P>That being said,&nbsp; I'd also like to address something else.&nbsp; There seems to be some confusion on exactly how the ' harmtouch ' ability works so I think I'll give a little lesson to those uninformed.&nbsp; Harmtouch is an instant cast spell with a range&nbsp;of 50 , that's it .... 50 ..... meaning .. if a cast time of even 1.0 sec was added to HT it could be easily outran.&nbsp; Then the only time the spell could be used practically would be if the intended victim was rooted.&nbsp; Well guess what, SK's don't get root and if my target is rooted in PvP, he's dead and there's no reason to use HT, I got a sword for that.</P>
<P>You say you want to see Harmtouch with a casting time like lifeburn or manaburn ?&nbsp; Great ... then put a 200 range on like manaburn and lifeburn and allow SK's the option to duck it off like any other spell.&nbsp; I personally think it will be&nbsp;funny as heck say to, stand on top of the building in PoValor and HT someone that will have no idea why they're watching &nbsp;<FONT color=#ff3300><STRONG>LOADING ... PLEASE WAIT </STRONG></FONT><FONT color=#cccccc>on their screen.&nbsp; As it is now, atleast with Harmtouch the way it is, the SK has to get right up in your face to use it, giving it a casting time and range gives a whole new meaning to the phrase " Tap / Tap / HT ".&nbsp; </FONT></P>
<DIV><FONT color=#ffff00><EM>Considering that most of VZ is now 4-teamers, Planar acceleration is now increased, and if you bring that point system over, it will be mainly affecting those who still remain Purist and those who still 3-team. - </EM></FONT><FONT color=#33cc00><STRONG>Coatlicueti</STRONG></FONT></DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><FONT color=#33cc00></FONT></STRONG>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV><FONT color=#cccccc>Coat, if you don't like 4 teaming then you don't have to look any further than the guild you are currently in so you know where to&nbsp;place the blame.&nbsp; Three teaming long killed the spirit of ' PvP Teams ' on Vallon Zek before&nbsp;Four teaming ever did.&nbsp; I stayed Dark Purist for my first 50+ levels ( back then 50 levels was a long time not like now where you can level from 1 to 50 in a day ) fighting the good fight against X-teaming Shorties / Humans / Elves that (&nbsp;by the terms others have used ) used an exploit of teaming together to further advance their PvE and PvP&nbsp;gains.&nbsp; The dark team ( while having greater numbers for a while ) did ok on the PvP front for a while, but the advancement of the Three-Team guilds caused an effect " gearflation " that was, in time, too difficult to over come with numbers.&nbsp; After a while, the numbers advantage of the dark team dwindled away as more and more joined Four-Team guilds or quit their dark characters and re-rolled ' Lighties ' to join the winning side.</FONT></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Three-Teaming is no better than Four-Teaming and the only people that truly have any room to complain about planar acceleration and gear imbalances are the few remaining purists on Vallon Zek.&nbsp; The fact that numbers have dwindled down even further on Vallon Zek has forced more and more once Three-Team guilds to go the route of Four-Team so they could simply field enough numbers to continue to push on thru Luclin and Planes of Power PvE content.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Vallon Zek will <STRONG>NEVER </STRONG>be a Team vs. Team server <STRONG>EVER </STRONG>again.&nbsp; Its a Guild vs. Guild server now with the exception of the few purists that remain.&nbsp; Nothing that can be said on this or any other post is going to change that.&nbsp; Ninty percent of Vallon is Four-Team .... if they were to Hardcode, 75% of that 90% would be gone.&nbsp; You'd have to condense all 4 Zeks into 1 server just to have enough people to throw together a ToV raid.&nbsp; Hardcode will never happen .... please purists give it a rest ..... that horse is dead so show&nbsp;it a little mercy and stop kicking it.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
