			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=DevCorner&message.id=7758#M7758">398</a> of 1058
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 13 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>This is gonna be LONG. This post should be reviewed by EVERYONE. Please feel free to pick apart ANYTHING that you think I have wrong here. This is an attempt to specifically describe changes that would "Balance" EQ PvP. Sony obviously doesn't have a clue, since they all play on blue servers anyway. I can prove that they don't play on PvP servers! Ever try to get a GM? Its nearly impossible on PvP servers.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>PLEASE NOTE: This is specifically for TEAM servers, NOT Rallos or Sullon. Some of these ideas could be used for them, but they are Very different in almost every PvP aspect from Vallon and Tallon. (Vallon and Tallon show how creative Sony can be, they changed 1 letter in the names of both servers.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>NOTE TO SONY: I WILL verbally /bash you in this post, since you have failed at so many attempts in EQ, and this looks like another, I don't feel I owe you the privaledge of respect at this point. After all, I pay to beta test a game that still hasn't had its original parts fixed. 5 years is a long time for a game to exist /congrats on that, but seriously. Have you ever released an expansion that worked? Kunark wasn't that bad, but I still have nightmares of Luclin. That was patcher hell when it went live. It didn't even have the bazaar /trader or /bazaar included, even though they were part of that expansion. DO NOT GET AHEAD OF YOURSELVES HERE. It would/could/WILL ruin game play. sorry if I get a bit out of line, but I've been playing a long time, I know how the system works. /ooc Darn PoK bug got me again. /ooc I'm back, sorry, EQ locked on me. I had to reset the comp... Again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ok, now that I have my insults out of the way, here is what I see as current issues, and possible fixes.<BR></DIV>
<DIV>Race/Class Combinations. (Currently on all servers)</DIV>
<DIV>Barbarian - BST, BER, ROG, SHM, WAR<BR>Dark Elf - CLR, ENC, MAG, NEC, ROG, SK, WAR, WIZ<BR>Dwarf - BER, CLR, PAL, ROG, WAR<BR>Erudite - CLR, ENC, MAG, NEC, PAL, SK, WIZ<BR>Froglok - CLR, PAL, SHM, WAR, WIZ<BR>Gnome - CLR, ENC, MAG, NEC, PAL, ROG, SK, WAR, WIZ<BR>Half Elf - BRD, DRU, PAL, RNG, ROG, WAR<BR>Halfling - CLR, DRU, PAL, RNG, ROG, WAR<BR>High Elf - CLR, ENC, MAG, PAL, WIZ<BR>Human - BRD, CLR, DRU, ENC, MAG, MNK, NEC, PAL, RNG, ROG, SK, WAR, WIZ<BR>Iksar - BST, MNK, NEC, SK, SHM, WAR<BR>Ogre - BST, BER, SK, SHM, WAR<BR>Troll - BST, BER, SK, SHM, WAR<BR>Vah Shir - BRD, BST, BER, ROG, SHM, WAR<BR>Wood Elf - BRD, DRU, RNG, ROG, WAR</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Teams (On Vallon and Tallon Zek)<BR>Blue (human) Team - BAR, ERU, FRG, HUM, VAH<BR>Orange (evil) Team - DE, OGR, TRL, IKS<BR>Purple (shorty (peck)) Team - DWF, GNM, Halfling<BR>Yellow (elf (fef)) Team - Half Elf, High elf, Wood elf</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Okay, now to fix current issues with just these aspects.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp; Think of being on evil team here. Nobody can track, nobody can be a bard. Some of the finer classes cannot be used because of race/class combos here. EVERY team should have access to the same classes. Some minor changes would enable darkies to play bards, Pallys or some of the other classes that they currently cannot. Half of the ballance issues are the classes, the other half are the teams. A poorly equiped team cannot win a long fight. Try to adjust things better. Also, who's crazy idea was it to put Frogloks on Human team??? They are very clearly shorties. Try to ballance any new races across the teams that are already short of races to play. Further examination into these Race/Class combos makes me wonder why a Dwarf can be a Berserker, but a human cannot. This whole Race/Class/Team system needs a little "twinking" to get it right. Its only been 5 years, you'll probably get around to these changes before EQ celebrates its tenth anniversary.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Next big thing. Class ballance.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Some games would make the classes Rock Paper Scissors. Warior beats hybrid - Hybrid beats caster - caster beats Warrior. However I think this is a bad way to "fix" PvP. Lets look at each class indevidually.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Bard = Uber powerful. Selos + anything = victory for Bard. I liked what someone posted about Bards not being able to cast more than 1 spell whith Selos. Casting 2 spells while using Selos would cancel Selos and the bard would return to his narmal run speed. More thought needs to go into these guys. Casting while running is just way too uber for PvP. However removing them from PvP servers might be a bit excessive. Try a few things, then /delete Bards from PvP servers.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Beastlord = Powerful class, but with some magor disadvantages in PvP. They have to rely heavily on their pets and as we all know from previous posts, pets are easy to remove from the PvP equation. Root/Fear/Snare are some very effective, easy solutions. Maybe pet classes should get a resist buff that only works on their pets. Something like the Magician pet heal spells. 60+ pet resist spells should add 200 resist to ALL resists to make sure the pet doesn't get rooted/feared/snared easily.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Berserker = Very strong class. They can use throwing axes to stun, snare and range attack any mob they want. They also have some very nice combat skills. I don't have a Berserker on a PvP server, so I'll leave them alone with this... Maybe they shoudl be able to use their axes to stun/snare players also. Would give them an edge for the melee classes.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Cleric = Uber healer/easy kill. Clerics can PvP IF they can get root to stick on the opponent long enough to land a heal on themselves. If a Cleric can resist the urge to nuke his target, he can save his/her mana for heals making the fight a very long one. Furthermore, AAs can make a Clerics Ecceptional Heals a real problem when he Complete heals off of a fast casting heal that normally wouldn't heal him much. However Clerics can't do much in the way of damage. They need some Major PvP spells added.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Druid = a great all around class. They just need some minor revamping to bring them back into the game again. Remember when everyone had a Druid? Somewhere along the line, they just stopped being needed because other classes could carry the load that Druids used to. Druids can be very powerful PKs, but should have some adjustments to make them more fun to PvE and PvP with.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Enchanter = Major pain in the rear is he gets a mez on ya. Been there, done that. Looted and scooted. Chanters need some reworks done on their spells. Being able to chain cast mez or stun on you just plain sux. They should have a delay on PvP targets. Maybe a message that says "You can not mez this player at this time." Until the delay from last mez wears off. This would allow melee types to actually deal some damage on them before they win.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Magician = Very powerful class. Until the pet gets Rooted/Feared/Snared and removed from the fight. A Magician can pop some very nasty Damage Shields and keep players from wanting to fight them. Again I come back to pet resist buff spells. Remember that Magicians can summon all kinds of stuff, the problem is that they can't summon much that is PvP specific, or PvP powerful.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Monk = One heck of a Melee class. If he can keep in contact with you, then you can forget casting on him. No fear, just use levitate, run up a hill, stand over top of him and cast away. Don't forget to keep your horse up and the Monk don't stand a chance. I'll talk about mounts later. Monks need some major PvP disciplines.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Necromancer = Second most powerful class in the game. Bards are easily the first, since Selos and casting while running was given to them. Necromancers can Life tap, which hurts you and heals them. The NEcro DoTs are insane also. Think of a 51 Necro using Splurt on a 43 anything. Unless the lvl 43 guy can cancel magic forever, the Necro wins. Necromancers don't really need any adjusting, they just should not be allowed to buff their pets past say 200 resists. Necros don't need pets to win in PvP.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Paladin = Decent hybrid class. LoH (Lay of Hands) is what sets them apart from any other class. An instant Complete Heal makes them a valuable ally in PvP. I'm not sure that Paladins need much changing either, except for that darn insta-cast mount.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ranger = Good overall class. Rangers have spells (they don't do a whole lot, but they have them) and they can snare. Snare can turn the tide of any battle, unless &lt;target&gt; has a mount.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Rogue = Minor threat. A Rogue can mess you up fast, but he is easily prevented from doing his best damage to you. All you have to do is prevent him from getting behind you, and his BS (Back Stab) is useless. Rogues need major PvP revamping.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Shadow Knight = Uber PvP class. HT or DT and its all over. Unless you decide to give everyone an insta-cast finishing blow, or like the pally and insta-cast uber heal/buff. these should be turned to PvE only. Remember, PvP is not supposed to be easy, its supposed to be fun. Tactics are what makes PvP great, and there haven't been much need of tactics in a WHILE. Remember when people used to hide behind objects and attack? Try using trees and such to shield you from vision. Granted with the current EQ settings you can be in the same hallway as your target and still "You cannot see your target". But I'll talk more on tactics later.</DIV>
<DIV>Shaman = Great class until around lvl 60 or so. Major high end PvP revamp required. People who play shamans PLEASE post more on this class.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Warrior = Awesome Melee class. Probably the single worst PvP class. Vertually no way to slow or stop his assailant. I think Warriors should get focuses, like Focused Will that would enable them to "Shadow Step" and Snare or Slow their opponent. Say they get a skill like Kick that allows them to "Bludgeon" their opponent slowing their attacks, or break their opponents arm or something. It would only work in PvP and would slow their target by a percentage based on the warriors lvl. At best this should be a 40% or 50% slow. Further more Warriors and other Melee classes should get the ability to slow casters. Example of caster spell window. Cast time: 4.0 Your time: 6.3. This would be Uber powerful for warriors. You enrage your opponent. You have been enraged, your thoughts slow. Think of the possiblilities to a war that can Shadow Step and slow casters cast times.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Wizard = What can I say. Wizard scores a critical blast. --LOADING... PLEASE WAIT. --</DIV>
<DIV>I think that covers all the classes. PLEASE EVERYONE, Build on what I've started and tell Sony EXACLY what we want. We know they'll never get it right if we don't spell it out with pictures included.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Mounts.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mounts can make meditating very easy in hostile areas. Mounts have many bonuses, but need to be cancelable. Cancel Magic MUST kill the mount. I hate to see my mount go, but I know that the melee classes need the ability. A new skill MUST be given to all Pure melee classes, and maybe to everyone. The skill could be called "Joust" or "Unass" (look up unass in the dictionary before nailing me for cussing). Unass would be a better word for the skill. It would kick the player off their mount and prevent them from summoning another mount for 2 minutes. Of course, you could FAIL to unass your opponent from their mount.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Tactics.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tactics have been used against me in PvP that have made me /tell PKer /congrats on that one. You really got me good =)<BR>Remember that hiding to prevent counter attacks is WISE not cowardly. Sometimes we get upset because the opponent out smarted us Big Time. Hiding inside buildings with an open end and casting long range spells is a great tactic, since the target must cover a large area of ground before he can counter attack. The idea of resists is ok, but lets face it, if we can ever reach a point where spells don't land, then PvP is pointless. At max resists a player should only resist 50% of spells thrown at them. Other wise I should get saves versus melee, this would enable me to become imune to combat damage from that hybrid beating me down. Use ANY tactic that helps you win. But keep honor, Please. Portal camping is a pain in the rear end. Especially if you get Corpse Camped there. Also remeber Zone Camping is very bad to do. Don't attack a character as soon as they appear, wait until they bounce or start to move. This means that the player has gained control of the character and is now able to defend himself.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>/Afk.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp; I have felt for some time that /AFK should render the player Invulnerable. Naturally a player should not be able to go /AFK as soon as he/she is low health. /AFK should sit the character down and prevent ANY kind of activity from that char, since the player is away from the keyboard anyway. This would prevent players from killing /AFK people. Remember the old Classic EQ adage? AFK = Another Friggin Kill. This idea needs some thought. Maybe you cannot go /afk for 2 mins after combat has finished, or maybe Invulnerability should only kick in 30 seconds after the player goes AFK. Consider this idea, give lots of feedback. I've had this idea for more than a year now, I just haven't thought about how to actually implement it without it becoming a PvP saving tactic.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Epics.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp; If you really plan on bringing PvP back to our servers, then you really need to change a few things that helped Kill PvP in the first place. Epic mobs in Nektulos forrest for Paladins. This was a very Lame idea. Not one darkie race can be pally, yet they have an epic mob in their newbie area. Bad PvP move. Ever Epic should be reconsidered based on PvP. If an epic mob spawns in such a place, the mob should be moved to a place where a player can actually kill the mob. I can see Defiant now. All they need to do is camp the zone and kill everyone who wants to kill the guard that Pallys need for their Epic. Easy PvP.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>PvP.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp; THIS IS PvP WE DO NOT WORK TOGETHER. Asking us to share space is what has been killing PvP in the first place.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Safe Zones.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes, Safe zones did hurt PvP, BUT do you really feel like going back to tradeskilling in PvP areas? How many people are addicted to C3/KEI or Virtue? You can kiss those nice buffs good bye when they take away safe zones. I know you all think the bazaar is gonna be the new happinin' place, but it just isn't gonna work like that. Removing Nexus is a dumb Idea too. I never really understood why Nexus wasn't PvP enabled, but think of it this way. PoK and Bazaar non PvP. The only zone between them is Nexus, Leave it safe. PoT also should remain safe, unless you wanna add a large desert zone between PoK and PoT. You could make it like WK or WC. The PoT stone would take you to this large zone full of PvP, then player could cross it on the way to PoT. PoT would also have to be changed, but it would make clicking out to escape certain death a lot harder. Remember Classic EQ guys! That is our PvP goal here. We didn't have safe zones, but we didn't have buffs either. Safe zones did take away some PvP opertunity, but they gave us the buffs and the gear. /cringes at the thought of G'Fay Mart.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Race Wars.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; We are Race war servers. This can be fixed without hard coding things. Simply remove ALL Experience modifiers if the group is not one single solitary team. Hunting in ANY zone, even hotspots would remove ALL bonuses if 1 char from another team was in the group/raid. Encourage race wars, don't force them.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>PvP 1 on 1<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Remeber that ALL PvP should be based on 1 on 1 fights. Mass PvP has always been out of balance. The bottom line is that a Warrior needs the same chance to win against a Cleric or a Necromancer. Just keep each class in balance with Every other class. This is not easy, I know. But can be done by making some classes more powerful with Combat Disciplines and spells.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Challenge.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The reward should NEVER be points. Reward for PvP is over coming the challenge of the oponnent. PvE = fighting a computer. It can only do a couple moves. Fighting PvP means the opponents can do ANYHTING. PvP will always be more exciting than PvE. Back in Classic EQ, I remember when you rarely saw someone with a last name. So few people had made it to the top. Velious was the beggining of the end because anyone was then able to reach lvl 60. Then came Luclin, and the game lost all its challenge. The game was awesome when there were so few at the top. Durring this time, I was at the botom, and I still liked it. I still get a thrill from narrowly escaping PvP. I get a real rush though, from winning PvP. Make the game hard again. The little things make the game great. Remeber, The point isn't that we CAN tradeskill. Its WHAT we can tradeskill and make. Small things often make or break an idea.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Level Caps for PvP.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; On Vallon and Tallon we have an 8 level cap. This means that a lvl 57 can be PKed by a lvl 65 with Uber Po Time gear. This is so unfair. I suggest a revamp of the PvP level range. Lets say its 5 levels from lvl 10 to lvl 40. This means that at the most, the opponent will have his next set of spells more powerful than yours. With 8 lvls, he can be 2 spell sets ahead of you. levels 40 to 50 should be 3 levels. Since players are becoming more powerful, it stands to reason that we narrow the gap a bit. 51 to 63 could be 2 levels. This still means a lot of power in spells. Levels 64+ should only be able to PvP 1 lvl diff. This means that at lvl 65 you could only PvP someone lvl 64 or lvl 66. Since OoW is on its way, I presume lvl 70 will be the new max. This still doesn't help Joeshmoe who is lvl 65 and doesn't have any planes flags yet who is fighting JacktheRipper who is flagged for Po Time and has Uber gear. I recomend that Flags are also used in determining if a player is a legal PvP target. This way a player flagged for Po Time could not PvP a player who is flagged for Po Time, and there for should help balance the PvP a bit. Yes I know that when JoeShmoe gets flagged he still doesn't have any of the Po Time gear, but he can finally get it. Also he should have gear from the previous planes tier that he fought on. So the fight still isn't too unbalanced. But, Like I said before, PLEASE submit feedback to say where I am wrong with this post.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Death Effects.<BR>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; PvP death should result in Respawn with gear on, just like a lvl 2 PC who died, this saves LnS. You don't need Rez effects, but I like my idea of Death Effects. Death Effects do NOT cripple you in ANY way, but they do lock you out of the zone you just died in. They last for 1 hour Real Time (the standard LnS time) You would get them "like" Rez effects from PvP deaths. Instead of Death effects saying "Death Effects" when you hold the aly key, or hover the mouse over them, it would say "Plane of Virtue" or "Everfrost Peaks" So you would know where you are locked from and the effects would fade when the time is up. This WILL prevent Bind rushing. Also the idea of PvP deaths forcing respawns in Shadowrest, bad idea. I just med a bit then Gate to my bind point and I'm set to bind rush. Next issue... What if I am bound in the zone I just got killed in. The game would then spawn you in a safe zone (See we need them) like PoK where you can sit and listen to people /auction stuff they couldn't sell in the bazaar. From PoK you can use a portal stone to get to a new Exp area, and life continues. Does anyone else like my idea??</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Ok, for now this is all I have to say. I'm sure I'll be back though. Have a great day, and sorry the post was so long, but it takes a long time to say a lot of things.</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
